Articles.Content:
I am looking for anyone who can help me out as I really want to make custom IVA's 

Recently, I started trying to mod IVA's from internals from mods (airplaneplus, bdarmory etc), but my problem is whenever I try to load JSIMainCompUnit or any switch or dial using PartTools 2017.3 ver 1.0.56 for that matter, Unity 2019.4.18f1 gives me console messages of the following:

Cannot clone model 'ASET/ASET_Props/Control/Push_Button_Modular/models/pb_SplitVertical_Cap' as model does not exist

P.S: I have also used TMPro 2017 and uninstalled the one that came with the unity version mentioned above

 

I tried to follow this forum: 

 

SOLVED ISSUE:

1 thing: DONT BE LAZY

errors were showing up due to the .cfg trying to spawn something in from a folder OUTSIDE of the set Gamedata directory

simple terms: part tools couldn't find the model that the .cfg file was trying to load because it was outside of the folder in which part tools was searching in.

 

 

sorry for the bother, and if any soul happens to come across this thread i hope this can help

solved my issue
